abstract: Delta reports that its earnings rose 51 percent, with net income of $549 million, or 65 cents a share, up from $363 million, or 43 cents a share a year earlier; revenue rose 10 percent to $9.8 billion; Delta's shares felll 46 cents, or 5.2 percent to $8.44, down 33 percent for the year.
snippet: Although the carrier reduced flights, business travel remained strong for the third quarter.
lead_paragraph: Although the carrier reduced flights, business travel remained strong for the third quarter.

headline.seo: Higher Fares Bolster Delta’s Earnings by 51%
